File Structure

```
OnlineAuction/
│
├── data/
│   ├── auctions.txt
│   ├── categories.txt
│   ├── bids.txt
│   ├── bid_history.txt
│   ├── items.txt
│   └── trending.txt
│
├── templates/
│   ├── auction_dashboard.html
│   ├── auction_catalog.html
│   ├── auction_details.html
│   ├── place_bid.html
│   ├── bid_history.html
│   ├── categories.html
│   ├── winners.html
│   ├── trending.html
│   └── status.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (auction item images like watch.jpg, desk.jpg, etc.)
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

Descriptions:

- `data/`  
  Contains all local text files storing application data in the specified formats:  
  - `auctions.txt`: Auction details including auction_id, item_name, description, category, starting_bid, current_bid, end_time, status, image_url.  
  - `categories.txt`: Categories data with category_id, category_name, description, item_count.  
  - `bids.txt`: Bid records with bid_id, auction_id, bidder_name, bid_amount, bid_timestamp.  
  - `bid_history.txt`: Historical bid data with history_id, auction_id, auction_name, bidder_name, bid_amount, bid_timestamp.  
  - `items.txt`: Item details including item_id, auction_id, item_name, starting_price, category, condition, seller_name.  
  - `trending.txt`: Trending auctions data with relevant metrics.

- `templates/`  
  HTML files for each page of the web application, structured to include the required elements and IDs as per the requirements:  
  - `auction_dashboard.html`: Main hub page showing featured auctions and navigation buttons.  
  - `auction_catalog.html`: Page listing all available auctions with search and filter inputs.  
  - `auction_details.html`: Detailed view of a specific auction with bid history and place bid button.  
  - `place_bid.html`: Form page for users to place a bid on an auction.  
  - `bid_history.html`: Page displaying all bids with filtering and sorting options.  
  - `categories.html`: Page listing all auction categories with descriptions and counts.  
  - `winners.html`: Page showing all won items with filtering by winner name.  
  - `trending.html`: Page displaying trending auctions with time range filter.  
  - `status.html`: Page showing status of all auctions with filtering and refresh button.

- `static/`  
  Contains static assets:  
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.  
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity, navigation, filtering, sorting, and form validation.  
  - `images/`: Folder for auction item images referenced in auctions data.

- `app.py`  
  The main Python application file implementing the backend logic to read/write data from/to text files, handle routing, render templates, and process user actions like placing bids.

- `requirements.txt`  
  Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask).

- `README.md`  
  Documentation describing setup, running instructions, and overview of the application.

This structure supports a modular, maintainable web application fulfilling all specified requirements using Python and local text file data storage.
